WEBVTT

00:00.670 --> 00:01.710
- Previously on
"Nashville"...

00:01.710 --> 00:03.790
- Can you just stop
for a minute?

00:03.790 --> 00:04.830
- What's going on?

00:04.830 --> 00:06.290
- I feel like
I can't feel myself.

00:06.290 --> 00:08.830
- Juliette Barnes'
new album, "Grateful"...

00:08.830 --> 00:10.290
- It's a bold attempt
at a crossover,

00:10.290 --> 00:12.960
but the result
is a treacly mess.

00:12.960 --> 00:16.670
- Want me to read your palm?

00:16.670 --> 00:18.540
- I'm pregnant.
- Your friend's cheek swab

00:18.540 --> 00:20.380
will tell the lab
whether he is a match.

00:20.380 --> 00:22.170
- It doesn't matter.
I still love you.

00:22.170 --> 00:24.750
- Bucky can be less than
receptive to new ideas.

00:24.750 --> 00:25.790
Well I wanna know what you think

00:25.790 --> 00:27.040
about finding another
job for him.

00:27.040 --> 00:29.120
- You wanna let him go,
is what you want.

00:30.790 --> 00:35.460
(crowd chanting)
- Juliette! Juliette!

00:38.080 --> 00:40.290
- Miss Barnes, you okay?

00:40.290 --> 00:42.880
(crowd chanting)
- Juliette! Juliette!

00:47.120 --> 00:49.040
- How long now?

00:49.040 --> 00:50.830
- First time a few months ago,

00:50.830 --> 00:53.620
and then nothing
until last week.

00:53.620 --> 00:54.960
- Where were you
a few months ago?

00:54.960 --> 00:59.380
I was rehearsing
a song I never sang.

00:59.380 --> 01:01.120
- I'm going to refer you
to a psychiatrist I know.

01:01.120 --> 01:05.120
- No, no, I don't have time
to talk to anybody else.

01:05.120 --> 01:07.040
Can't you fix this?

01:07.040 --> 01:08.120
- This isn't
a neurological problem.

01:08.120 --> 01:11.420
- I have a show tomorrow night.

01:11.420 --> 01:13.880
- Well, what you're describing,

01:13.880 --> 01:15.580
the uh, sensory disturbances,

01:15.580 --> 01:17.750
out of body experience,

01:17.750 --> 01:19.540
are the signs
of a dissociative state.

01:19.540 --> 01:21.460
- What does that mean?

01:21.460 --> 01:23.670
- Well, it's one of the brain's
earliest defense systems,

01:23.670 --> 01:25.040
like playing dead.

01:25.040 --> 01:26.460
Some people faint,

01:26.460 --> 01:28.380
some people have what you have.

01:28.380 --> 01:30.290
Some people become catatonic.

01:30.290 --> 01:31.710
- Defense against what?

01:31.710 --> 01:33.170
- Trauma.

01:33.170 --> 01:35.960
- Oh, again with the crash.
- Well, maybe.

01:35.960 --> 01:38.960
But more often, this comes
from uh, childhood trauma.

01:38.960 --> 01:41.960
Did anything bad happen
when you were little?

01:41.960 --> 01:43.380
- Don't ask.

01:43.380 --> 01:45.170
- Her father died
when she was four.

01:45.170 --> 01:47.920
- I don't even remember him.

01:47.920 --> 01:51.210
Can any of this
possibly be helping?

01:51.210 --> 01:53.250
What am I going to do
about tomorrow night?

01:53.250 --> 01:56.670
- The smartest thing
is to avoid stress.

01:56.670 --> 01:58.210
I would cancel.

02:00.880 --> 02:02.540
- I know what this is.

02:02.540 --> 02:03.960
When did the album
reviews come out?

02:03.960 --> 02:05.380
- What are you talking about?

02:05.380 --> 02:07.750
- Exactly when this started
to happen again.

02:07.750 --> 02:10.290
- So what, this is some sort
of bad review reaction?

02:10.290 --> 02:13.040
- My brain can't
process failure.

02:13.040 --> 02:15.210
I cringe still
when I think about it.

02:15.210 --> 02:16.920
- Then maybe you should cancel.

02:16.920 --> 02:19.170
I mean, they can find
someone to fill the spot.

02:19.170 --> 02:21.960
- I don't want anybody
filling my spot.

02:21.960 --> 02:23.670
- So then do it.

02:23.670 --> 02:25.380
- That's the thing that's
stressing me out.

02:25.380 --> 02:27.000
- What do you want me to say?

02:27.000 --> 02:28.830
(phone rings)
- I don't know.

02:28.830 --> 02:30.710
- Hello?

02:30.710 --> 02:32.120
I know we're up first.

02:32.120 --> 02:34.460
I'm on my way.
Just hold on.

02:34.460 --> 02:36.330
- Don't worry about it.
Okay, I have an idea

02:36.330 --> 02:37.620
and you have
a festival to open,

02:37.620 --> 02:40.790
so why don't you go.
Go, go.

02:40.790 --> 02:43.750
- You got that weird
look in your eye.

02:43.750 --> 02:45.210
- Baby, you are going
to do such a great job,

02:45.210 --> 02:46.790
I know you are,

02:46.790 --> 02:49.920
and I will meet you
after my rehearsal.

02:49.920 --> 02:52.670
- Okay, first: interviews.
Here's the deal.

02:52.670 --> 02:54.250
Just say a few words about
tomorrow's performance,

02:54.250 --> 02:55.670
how it feels to work
with Juliette,

02:55.670 --> 02:57.420
keep it light,
you'll be great. Okay?

02:57.420 --> 02:59.540
(phone rings)
- Juliette, hey.

02:59.540 --> 03:01.000
- I want to do it alone.

03:01.000 --> 03:03.170
- Want to do what alone?
- Tomorrow night.

03:03.170 --> 03:05.080
- Wh--Well,
I hate to tell you this,

03:05.080 --> 03:07.040
but that ship has sailed.

03:07.040 --> 03:08.420
- The ship has not sailed,

03:08.420 --> 03:09.880
I say when ships sail,

03:09.880 --> 03:12.330
and I'm saying this ship
has not sailed.

03:12.330 --> 03:14.460
- Juliette, we are
less than 40 hours away

03:14.460 --> 03:16.000
from this performance.

03:16.000 --> 03:17.540
- Good, that will be
a perfect amount of time

03:17.540 --> 03:18.540
for me to rehearse.

03:18.540 --> 03:20.210
- All right, you know what?

03:20.210 --> 03:21.960
Then you're going to have
to tell him yourself.

03:21.960 --> 03:23.420
- Fine.

03:25.880 --> 03:29.830
♪ I've got to be direct ♪

03:32.580 --> 03:36.620
♪ If I'm wrong
please correct ♪

03:39.750 --> 03:43.790
♪ You're standing on my neck ♪

03:43.790 --> 03:45.170
(text message rings)

03:46.830 --> 03:48.000
- That's interesting,
what is that?

03:48.000 --> 03:50.620
- Nothing.

03:50.620 --> 03:52.380
- Hey guys.

03:52.380 --> 03:54.120
- Hey, oh, sweetie,
I was thinking,

03:54.120 --> 03:55.580
maybe the three of us
could all go down

03:55.580 --> 03:56.750
to the festival together today,

03:56.750 --> 03:57.750
you know, like a family deal.

03:57.750 --> 03:59.420
What do you think, that be good?

03:59.420 --> 04:01.290
- I'm going to meet
Louisa at the mall.

04:01.290 --> 04:03.330
- And I was supposed to be at
Tracks ten minutes ago,

04:03.330 --> 04:05.460
and then I'm going
to the festival with Clay.

04:05.460 --> 04:06.540
- (sighs) All right.

04:06.540 --> 04:08.210
Uh...hey, how about we--

04:08.210 --> 04:11.000
- Dad, we love you,
but we're fine.

04:11.000 --> 04:12.120
- You're fine?

04:12.120 --> 04:13.960
- Yeah, we're fine.

04:13.960 --> 04:16.750
- What about you, Daphne?

04:16.750 --> 04:20.000
You doing okay,
need a ride or anything?

04:20.000 --> 04:21.830
- Yes, and no.

04:25.290 --> 04:27.880
- Well, all right then.

04:27.880 --> 04:30.120
- You can see it
for yourself, Alicia,

04:30.120 --> 04:32.500
this crowd is so ready
for the final two nights

04:32.500 --> 04:34.750
of Music City's Music Week.

04:34.750 --> 04:36.880
We got Dierk's Bentley,
Little Big Town,

04:36.880 --> 04:38.500
Chris Stapleton,
The Exes, and of course,

04:38.500 --> 04:41.540
the first live performance
by Juliette Barnes

04:41.540 --> 04:44.290
since that plane crash
earlier this year.

04:44.290 --> 04:45.920
- So aside from bringing
you a new artist,

04:45.920 --> 04:48.750
I was thinking about big
media integration--uh, Deacon!

04:48.750 --> 04:50.500
Just the man I want to see,
let me introduce you to Casadee.

04:50.500 --> 04:52.290
- I know Deacon.
- Hey, Cass.

04:52.290 --> 04:55.170
- How you doing?

04:55.170 --> 04:57.420
Look, I like the changes
you guys have been making,

04:57.420 --> 04:59.420
so let's set something up.
- Yeah.

04:59.420 --> 05:02.420
- All right, yeah.
- Great. Oh...

05:02.420 --> 05:04.040
Uh, you mind if we take
a walk for a second?

05:05.790 --> 05:06.830
- Yeah.
- Okay.

05:06.830 --> 05:08.790
So I hate to bring this up,

05:08.790 --> 05:10.080
but have you given it
anymore thought?

05:10.080 --> 05:11.790
- You talking about Bucky?

05:11.790 --> 05:13.540
- I'm talking about moving
the company forward.

05:13.540 --> 05:14.920
- Bucky's been a part
of this business,

05:14.920 --> 05:16.790
part of this family
for over 30 years.

05:16.790 --> 05:18.620
So no, there's no way.
- Can I ask how the company's

05:18.620 --> 05:20.250
done over the last couple years?

05:20.250 --> 05:21.330
Layla Grant, Markus Keen,
Vita Martin.

05:21.330 --> 05:22.830
- That's not all on Bucky,

05:22.830 --> 05:24.750
there's a whole lot
of things that happened.

05:24.750 --> 05:26.880
- Whatever it was,
it's time Highway 65

05:26.880 --> 05:29.380
stops missing
opportunities, okay?

05:29.380 --> 05:30.670
Maddie's single
is ready for release

05:30.670 --> 05:32.580
and I don't want
to stand by and watch

05:32.580 --> 05:34.330
the same archaic protocols
take her down.

05:34.330 --> 05:36.080
- Okay, what does
that mean, exactly?

05:36.080 --> 05:38.380
- Well, for Maddie, I was
thinking a midnight release.

05:38.380 --> 05:40.750
No press, no announcements.

05:40.750 --> 05:42.290
No begging some
reporter at Slate

05:42.290 --> 05:44.000
to give us a mention
under the fold.

05:44.000 --> 05:45.420
No, no, no,
we release it ourselves,

05:45.420 --> 05:47.000
we get all
the influencers we know

05:47.000 --> 05:49.540
to talk about this amazing
song they just heard

05:49.540 --> 05:52.460
and in the morning,
everyone comes to us, man.

05:52.460 --> 05:56.120
- Huh.
- Yeah.

05:57.830 --> 05:59.670
- What about Bucky,
does he agree?

05:59.670 --> 06:01.080
- Not only does Bucky not agree,

06:01.080 --> 06:03.250
he doesn't even
understand it, Deacon.

06:03.250 --> 06:05.750
And I'm sorry, but I think
this is a move that is essential

06:05.750 --> 06:10.290
if we want Highway 65
and Maddie to succeed.

06:10.290 --> 06:11.920
In a way that I think
Rayna would have wanted.

06:16.670 --> 06:18.120
(rock music plays)

06:32.460 --> 06:34.000
- Hey.

06:34.000 --> 06:35.580
- Huh, can't get enough
of the sweet life?

06:35.580 --> 06:37.500
- Something like that.

06:37.500 --> 06:40.170
What is all this, can I help?

06:40.170 --> 06:41.500
- My fan mail.

06:42.960 --> 06:45.170
- You're new.

06:45.170 --> 06:47.710
- Yeah, I'm Daphne.

06:47.710 --> 06:49.580
- I wasn't asking.

06:49.580 --> 06:50.830
- She's cool, Wendy,
she's with me.

06:50.830 --> 06:52.420
- I don't like new.

06:52.420 --> 06:55.290
New comes with motives
and problems.

06:55.290 --> 06:57.460
- I'm just here to see Liv.

06:57.460 --> 06:58.830
- Liv's busy.

06:58.830 --> 07:00.170
- Where are you guys going?

07:00.170 --> 07:02.120
- New is also very nosy.

07:02.120 --> 07:04.790
- No! Stop being a bitch.

07:04.790 --> 07:06.170
Chill.

07:07.670 --> 07:09.580
- Can I come?

07:14.080 --> 07:15.830
- So I was thinking we can
start with The Rumble?

07:15.830 --> 07:17.500
- Yeah, I was going to
talk to you about that.

07:17.500 --> 07:18.620
(phone vibrates)
Crap.

07:18.620 --> 07:20.830
- What?
- Nothing.

07:22.580 --> 07:24.040
- You can't keep avoiding him.

07:24.040 --> 07:25.460
- Well, I can until I can't.

07:25.460 --> 07:26.960
- What does that even mean?

07:26.960 --> 07:28.830
(phone vibrates)
- Double crap.

07:39.460 --> 07:41.620
- This idea of a midnight
release is a risk, guys,

07:41.620 --> 07:43.210
and it's just a risk
I don't think

07:43.210 --> 07:44.710
we should be taking
with your first single.

07:44.710 --> 07:46.710
- But I love the idea
of putting it out there

07:46.710 --> 07:48.420
and letting it speak for itself.

07:48.420 --> 07:50.330
- Well, it will, but people
have to know about it,

07:50.330 --> 07:52.250
you know, we don't want it to be
a tree falling in the forest.

07:52.250 --> 07:54.880
It's a great single, I think
it deserves a proper rollout.

07:54.880 --> 07:57.830
- Dad?

07:57.830 --> 07:59.750
- I got to go with Bucky,
you know, I mean,

07:59.750 --> 08:01.960
He's right, it is great,
and we want to do it the way--

08:01.960 --> 08:05.000
- Hey, sorry I'm late.

08:05.000 --> 08:06.710
Must have missed the memo.

08:06.710 --> 08:08.420
Maddie, it's great to see you,
how are you doing?

08:08.420 --> 08:10.040
- Nice to see you.
Awesome.

08:10.040 --> 08:11.830
- Have you been telling her
about our cool plan

08:11.830 --> 08:15.290
for the release.
I am stoked.

08:15.290 --> 08:17.210
- Can you two give us
a quick sec?

08:17.210 --> 08:18.880
- Sure.
- Thank you.

08:22.380 --> 08:24.170
- Hey, Bucky, what do you
think of this...

08:24.170 --> 08:25.750
- What are you doing?

08:25.750 --> 08:27.460
- What I think needs to be done.

08:27.460 --> 08:30.460
- He's staying.
- Because he's family?

08:30.460 --> 08:32.960
- Yeah, because we need him.

08:34.880 --> 08:37.380
- Deacon, this company
may need many things,

08:37.380 --> 08:41.330
but I assure you,
Bucky isn't one of them.

08:41.330 --> 08:43.040
- I fly to the coast
on Monday morning,

08:43.040 --> 08:45.040
it would be awesome if
you gave me an answer before--

08:45.040 --> 08:46.790
- Pretty sure I just did.

08:46.790 --> 08:48.250
- Just do me a favor

08:48.250 --> 08:50.670
and think it through
for the next 24 hours

08:50.670 --> 08:53.580
with your head
instead of your heart.

08:53.580 --> 08:55.000
That always helps me.

09:01.790 --> 09:03.540
- Is everything okay?

09:03.540 --> 09:06.830
I thought rehearsal
didn't start for another hour.

09:06.830 --> 09:09.500
- Something came up.

09:09.500 --> 09:13.210
It's the label,
they are in full blown panic.

09:13.210 --> 09:18.620
I--I'm so sorry, this is,
this is terrible--they...

09:18.620 --> 09:20.750
they don't want me
promoting the album

09:20.750 --> 09:21.790
at tomorrow night's show.

09:21.790 --> 09:23.290
- I don't understand.

09:23.290 --> 09:25.540
- They want me to play
some of my old stuff,

09:25.540 --> 09:27.540
stuff they know works.

09:27.540 --> 09:28.960
And they want me to do it alone.

09:28.960 --> 09:30.330
- I can't believe this.

09:30.330 --> 09:31.960
We have been working so hard.

09:31.960 --> 09:34.880
- I can't believe it either.

09:34.880 --> 09:37.380
And, I promise you,
I will make this up to you.

09:37.380 --> 09:41.210
We have that mini tour
already set in place,

09:41.210 --> 09:43.210
and five shows.

09:43.210 --> 09:47.960
It's just the label has put
so much money into this album,

09:47.960 --> 09:50.830
they feel like if I can come
back with something familiar,

09:50.830 --> 09:52.830
then they can recoup
some of their losses.

09:52.830 --> 09:55.080
- They can't do this.

09:55.080 --> 09:57.620
- They already have.

09:57.620 --> 09:58.830
I wish...

10:04.290 --> 10:06.250
- Are you okay?

10:13.330 --> 10:17.120
- I just keep getting
these foggy episodes.

10:17.120 --> 10:20.500
- Oh, I'm sorry.

10:20.500 --> 10:24.420
- The doctor says
it's stress related.

10:24.420 --> 10:26.960
- Okay, come on, sit down.
Sit down.

10:30.880 --> 10:33.250
Okay, now look.

10:33.250 --> 10:37.290
I want you to take in
deep breaths, slow.

10:37.290 --> 10:39.670
Slow...
Breathe deep.

10:39.670 --> 10:43.790
and I want you to concentrate
on your safe place.

10:43.790 --> 10:45.750
- My what?

10:45.750 --> 10:49.540
- Home or the beach or you know,

10:49.540 --> 10:52.830
any image that makes you
feel comforted, you know?

10:52.830 --> 10:54.540
It--it totally works,

10:54.540 --> 10:56.830
I do it anytime I'm anxious,
okay, so just breathe.

10:59.420 --> 11:01.710
Okay? Breathe...

11:06.000 --> 11:09.170
- Okay, you ready?

11:09.170 --> 11:11.750
- Ready.

11:11.750 --> 11:14.210
- Happiest yellow,
just like you wanted.

11:19.210 --> 11:22.920
- You okay?

11:22.920 --> 11:24.710
- Yeah.

11:27.420 --> 11:29.710
- What are we doing here?
- Looking for things to sell.

11:29.710 --> 11:32.170
You wouldn't believe how much
valuable crap people throw away.

11:32.170 --> 11:34.500
- This is private property.
That's stealing.

11:34.500 --> 11:36.380
- You can't steal
what's already stolen.

11:36.380 --> 11:37.460
- What do you mean?

11:37.460 --> 11:38.790
- This guy takes in stolen goods

11:38.790 --> 11:40.380
and sells them
to the highest bidder,

11:40.380 --> 11:41.960
so it's like we're
hurting the bad guys.

11:41.960 --> 11:44.580
- Okay, two wrongs
don't really make a right.

11:44.580 --> 11:46.830
- So honest and naïve.
I like New.

11:46.830 --> 11:48.500
- Aren't you coming?

11:48.500 --> 11:51.120
- No, I'm fine here.
- All right, suit yourself.

11:52.580 --> 11:53.880
- Wait.

11:53.880 --> 11:55.540
- Hey!
- Let's go!

11:55.540 --> 11:57.000
- Get back here,
you little punk!

11:57.000 --> 11:58.620
- No!
Hurry up you guys!

12:04.330 --> 12:06.620
- Where'd you go?
- (screaming)

12:06.620 --> 12:08.830
- Come here!
come here!

12:11.880 --> 12:13.170
- Let go, dude!

12:18.620 --> 12:20.460
- Liv!

12:22.670 --> 12:25.040
- (screams)

12:29.460 --> 12:32.750
- Owww!
- Yo, hold still.

12:32.750 --> 12:35.790
- Oh my god!
- Hold--hold still.

12:35.790 --> 12:37.790
- You need to go to a hospital.
- No, no hospitals!

12:37.790 --> 12:39.330
- Why not?

12:39.330 --> 12:40.750
- Because hospitals ask
questions and want names.

12:40.750 --> 12:43.080
- Wrap it!
- You're not staying still.

12:43.080 --> 12:44.750
- Liv, listen to me, you're
going to get an infection.

12:44.750 --> 12:46.540
- Daphne, why are
you here, anyways?

12:46.540 --> 12:48.250
Just go!

12:51.290 --> 12:53.460
- Can't say I'm surprised.

12:53.460 --> 12:56.500
- This wasn't her choice.
- And who told you that?

12:56.500 --> 12:58.460
I told y'all this was a mistake
from the beginning.

12:58.460 --> 13:00.210
- She doesn't give
a damn about us.

13:00.210 --> 13:01.920
- Look, the label doesn't
think that this music--

13:01.920 --> 13:03.960
- Oh, come on, Hallie.
It's bad enough she lies,

13:03.960 --> 13:05.620
now she's using you
to deliver the bad news?

13:05.620 --> 13:06.750
- The label panicked.

13:06.750 --> 13:08.710
What can she do?

13:08.710 --> 13:10.540
You know, she kept her word
about the album.

13:10.540 --> 13:12.290
The mini tour.

13:12.290 --> 13:13.500
She's going
to make it up to us.

13:18.420 --> 13:20.790
(crowd cheering)
(guitar chord rings)

13:20.790 --> 13:22.120
- One, two!

13:22.120 --> 13:23.790
♪ I just spin my wheels ♪

13:23.790 --> 13:26.290
♪ But digging my heels in ♪

13:26.290 --> 13:30.250
♪ If hope is so close,
then why do I feel so alone ♪

13:33.540 --> 13:37.380
♪ Knowing what I know ♪

13:37.380 --> 13:41.750
♪ I keep headed for home,
but everyone's gone ♪

13:41.750 --> 13:46.580
♪ My favorite songs
make me feel so alone ♪

13:49.380 --> 13:51.880
♪ I keep headed for home ♪

13:51.880 --> 13:56.000
♪ I feel so alone ♪

13:56.000 --> 13:58.380
♪ But I keep headed for home ♪

14:01.500 --> 14:03.580
♪ Run with me
when hope is high ♪

14:03.580 --> 14:07.210
♪ Run with me
when the water is dry ♪

14:07.210 --> 14:09.380
♪ Never let me go ♪

