♪ Run with me into the night ♪

14:11.330 --> 14:15.120
♪ Run with me
to the morning light ♪

14:15.120 --> 14:16.540
♪ Never let me go ♪

14:24.170 --> 14:26.210
- You're still here?

14:26.210 --> 14:28.790
- Yeah, I like the furniture.

14:28.790 --> 14:30.920
- Sorry for yelling.

14:30.920 --> 14:32.920
- That's okay, my sister
yells at me all the time.

14:32.920 --> 14:35.080
(chuckles)

14:39.540 --> 14:41.120
- It'll be fine.

14:41.120 --> 14:43.120
- Okay, why are you here?
Where's your home?

14:43.120 --> 14:44.420
- This is home.

14:44.420 --> 14:45.920
- No, I mean,
where are your parents?

14:47.330 --> 14:48.790
- Are you referring

14:48.790 --> 14:50.500
to the biological drug addicts
that ditched me

14:50.500 --> 14:52.710
or the foster drunks that never
understood no meant no?

14:52.710 --> 14:55.670
- Wow.

14:55.670 --> 14:58.040
I'm really sorry.

14:58.040 --> 15:00.500
- I've survived way worse
than a stupid little cut.

15:00.500 --> 15:01.670
It'll be fine.

15:04.420 --> 15:06.380
- Yeah, it will.

15:06.380 --> 15:07.710
Cause you're coming
home with me.

15:11.580 --> 15:13.420
- Halfway through
the second verse...

15:13.420 --> 15:15.290
- Avery Barnes.
- Couldn't hear a thing.

15:15.290 --> 15:16.670
- Dude, Michael.
- Dude.

15:16.670 --> 15:18.170
You killed it.
- Thank you.

15:18.170 --> 15:20.080
- It was so good
seeing you out there, man.

15:20.080 --> 15:21.500
- Every person in that room

15:21.500 --> 15:23.880
can forget about
the rest of the festival

15:23.880 --> 15:26.380
because they just saw the best
damn act of the entire weekend.

15:26.380 --> 15:28.120
- Aw, no way, come on.

15:28.120 --> 15:29.500
- Oh yeah, then I won't
tell you, that uh,

15:29.500 --> 15:32.080
I just got you on
the Edward Sharpe tour.

15:32.080 --> 15:34.620
- Are you serious?
- I am.

15:34.620 --> 15:36.750
- What? Yes!

15:36.750 --> 15:38.540
- 20 cities.
You leave in ten days.

15:38.540 --> 15:41.000
Congratulations.
- 10 days?

15:42.500 --> 15:43.750
- Yeah, I get it.

15:43.750 --> 15:45.460
Discuss it with the boss
and let me know.

15:45.460 --> 15:47.000
They want an answer soon.

15:48.710 --> 15:51.710
- Yeah.

15:51.710 --> 15:54.040
- Play the track from the top
of the chorus again, please.

15:54.040 --> 15:56.500
(music plays)

15:58.080 --> 16:00.750
♪ This time it's
goodbye trouble ♪

16:00.750 --> 16:03.380
♪ I feel a light
at the end of this tunnel ♪

16:03.380 --> 16:06.960
♪ I get stronger
with every step ♪

16:08.830 --> 16:10.710
♪ Come hell--♪

16:10.710 --> 16:12.170
Ow!

16:20.380 --> 16:22.040
- You ready to get to it?

16:22.040 --> 16:23.710
- Okay.

16:23.710 --> 16:25.210
- I told you not
to walk away from me.

16:25.210 --> 16:26.750
- I said not in front
of Juliette.

16:26.750 --> 16:28.960
- I'm sick of you hiding
behind your little girl.

16:28.960 --> 16:30.380
You care more about that baby

16:30.380 --> 16:31.670
than you care about me,
don't you?

16:34.620 --> 16:36.750
- Hey, hey! Are you okay?
Are you okay?

16:36.750 --> 16:38.170
- Just get me out of here.

16:38.170 --> 16:39.670
- Come here, come here.

16:39.670 --> 16:41.120
I got you, I got you.
Come here.

16:41.120 --> 16:44.080
It's okay, I got you.
it's okay.

16:49.000 --> 16:51.830
- Just want to get some sleep.

16:51.830 --> 16:55.170
- No one says
you have to do this.

16:55.170 --> 16:59.000
- I say I have to do this.

16:59.000 --> 17:00.620
At this point,
I'm nearly forgotten.

17:00.620 --> 17:02.620
- Babe, you're out of your mind.

17:02.620 --> 17:05.120
People love you.

17:05.120 --> 17:07.330
- They used to love me.

17:09.920 --> 17:11.790
(text message rings)

17:24.750 --> 17:27.540
- Hello darling.
- Oh, hi.

17:30.120 --> 17:33.830
- (sighs) Look at you.

17:33.830 --> 17:35.620
Never agree to shoot a film
in Romania in the summer.

17:35.620 --> 17:39.080
It is hell, literally.
Shall we order a beverage?

17:39.080 --> 17:40.710
- Uh, look, I'm not sure

17:40.710 --> 17:42.290
if there's any proper way
to tell you this,

17:42.290 --> 17:44.420
so I'm just going to
spit it out.

17:44.420 --> 17:46.000
I'm pregnant.
- You're what?

17:46.000 --> 17:47.460
- And you're the father.

17:49.210 --> 17:51.170
- Okay, uh, uh, let's just
slow this down a bit.

17:51.170 --> 17:53.670
That's impossible.

17:53.670 --> 17:56.120
- You do understand
the process of conception?

17:56.120 --> 17:59.500
- Um, something to drink?

17:59.500 --> 18:02.880
- Grey Goose, straight up,
double it.

18:02.880 --> 18:04.880
- And for you?
- Water's fine, thank you.

18:07.540 --> 18:09.330
- We took precautions.

18:09.330 --> 18:12.040
- Which have been known to fail,
in case you haven't heard.

18:12.040 --> 18:13.380
- How do you even
know it's mine?

18:13.380 --> 18:15.000
- I don't like what
that insinuates,

18:15.000 --> 18:17.330
but a blood test
ruled out Gunnar.

18:17.330 --> 18:19.290
Look, I'm not telling you
this to stress you out

18:19.290 --> 18:21.210
or to turn your life upside
down, or anything like that,

18:21.210 --> 18:22.920
I just thought that you
should know I'm doing this.

18:22.920 --> 18:24.920
- You've decided to keep it.

18:24.920 --> 18:26.960
- Yeah.

18:26.960 --> 18:28.540
Thanks for making this
a horrible experience for me.

18:28.540 --> 18:30.420
- Wait.

18:30.420 --> 18:33.880
Don't leave, please.
Sit down.

18:35.620 --> 18:37.670
Look, I haven't
done this before.

18:37.670 --> 18:40.710
Faced this responsibility.

18:40.710 --> 18:42.080
I am sorry, really.

18:45.080 --> 18:46.580
- Neither have I.

18:49.250 --> 18:50.790
- Just tell me what you need,

18:50.790 --> 18:55.620
financially or...
whatever it is.

18:55.620 --> 18:57.210
Anything to make this
easier for you.

18:57.210 --> 18:59.580
- Easier for me?

18:59.580 --> 19:02.540
- Look, this was just
sort of sprung on me, I mean,

19:02.540 --> 19:03.960
you haven't even looked
at the bloody appetizers,

19:03.960 --> 19:05.330
and guess what, I'm a father.

19:10.000 --> 19:12.580
- This was a mistake.

19:26.710 --> 19:29.880
- Yo!
Yo, this is your house?

19:29.880 --> 19:32.170
Yo, you guys like
billionaires or something?

19:32.170 --> 19:33.500
- No, musicians.

19:33.500 --> 19:35.670
- Damn, billionaire musicians.

19:35.670 --> 19:37.420
- Follow me, I have stuff
for you in the bathroom.

19:37.420 --> 19:38.710
- Yeah, which wing
would that be in?

19:38.710 --> 19:40.330
(crowd cheering)
- Thank you!

19:40.330 --> 19:42.120
Thank you, Nashville!

19:42.120 --> 19:45.670
This has been so fantastic,
y'all have been so great.

19:45.670 --> 19:48.380
I can't tell you how much
it means to play here...

19:48.380 --> 19:50.880
- How'd it go with Damien?

19:50.880 --> 19:52.540
- I--I don't want to
talk about that name.

19:52.540 --> 19:56.790
- America's favorite
on again, off again couple,

19:56.790 --> 19:59.170
y'all give it up
for The Exes, come on.

19:59.170 --> 20:02.670
(crowd cheers)

