♪ 'Cause I love you
even when I don't ♪

21:11.000 --> 21:12.960
♪ I love you even when I don't ♪

21:12.960 --> 21:14.880
(knock on door)
- Hey.

21:14.880 --> 21:16.540
Hey, thanks for the text,
listen.

21:16.540 --> 21:18.750
I am completely out of the loop
on Maddie's single,

21:18.750 --> 21:20.670
and I'm pretty sure
Zach's trying to avoid me.

21:20.670 --> 21:23.380
He won't return my phone calls,
he won't return my emails.

21:23.380 --> 21:25.250
- Yeah, I know why.

21:25.250 --> 21:26.500
- What's going on?

21:31.330 --> 21:33.580
- He wants you out, Buck.

21:33.580 --> 21:36.330
- Out of what?
- Highway 65, everything.

21:39.380 --> 21:43.750
- Okay, um...

21:43.750 --> 21:45.210
Wow. I knew it was bad,

21:45.210 --> 21:46.500
but I didn't think
it was that bad.

21:46.500 --> 21:49.210
- I'm not going
to let it happen.

21:49.210 --> 21:50.880
- Deacon, you know how much
I care about you

21:50.880 --> 21:52.250
and the girls, and you know,

21:52.250 --> 21:54.500
my relationship with Ray--
- Hey, Buck,

21:54.500 --> 21:56.540
you don't have to
convince me, all right?

21:56.540 --> 21:59.460
We will figure this out.

22:04.170 --> 22:06.620
- Ready?
- No, um...

22:06.620 --> 22:09.120
- Sorry, Liv!
I--I'm sorry.

22:09.120 --> 22:11.330
- You don't plan on becoming
a doctor, were you? Ow!

22:11.330 --> 22:13.120
- You'll thank me
when I save your arm.

22:13.120 --> 22:16.040
- If I survive this torture.

22:16.040 --> 22:17.380
- You should stay here.

22:17.380 --> 22:20.620
- (laughs)
In your musical McMansion?

22:20.620 --> 22:23.710
Yeah, I'm sure your
parents would approve.

22:23.710 --> 22:25.290
- No, it's just Deacon,
he'll be fine with it.

22:25.290 --> 22:26.750
- What's a Deacon?

22:26.750 --> 22:28.670
- (laughing)
My step dad.

22:28.670 --> 22:31.500
- Oh, ha.

22:31.500 --> 22:33.000
Well, where's your real dad?

22:33.000 --> 22:34.250
- Oh, he's in jail.

22:34.250 --> 22:37.540
- What?
What about your mom?

22:37.540 --> 22:40.080
- She died.

22:40.080 --> 22:43.000
- Huh...

22:43.000 --> 22:45.000
Maybe you're my kind
of girl after all.

22:50.540 --> 22:52.380
- He can't do this.

22:52.380 --> 22:53.880
Bucky was with mom forever.

22:53.880 --> 22:55.460
Since she was a kid.

22:55.460 --> 22:56.750
- I know, sweetie,
so does he.

22:56.750 --> 22:58.790
Just doesn't care.
Hey honey.

22:58.790 --> 23:01.960
Don't worry,
I'll straighten it out.

23:01.960 --> 23:03.830
Oh, honey, I was about
to start dinner if you wait.

23:03.830 --> 23:05.580
- Oh, my stomach hurts.

23:05.580 --> 23:07.040
- I'm sorry.

23:09.580 --> 23:11.080
Oh come on, if you're
going to eat that much,

23:11.080 --> 23:12.620
just stay down here with us.

23:12.620 --> 23:14.580
- No, I was texting with Louisa

23:14.580 --> 23:16.170
and her stomach hurts too,

23:16.170 --> 23:18.880
so I think we may have
contracted something.

23:21.620 --> 23:23.540
- Does that seem odd to you?
- Completely.

23:31.500 --> 23:33.460
- Happy birthday my jewel.

23:33.460 --> 23:36.210
I thought this might complete
our happiest yellow home.

23:36.210 --> 23:38.960
- I thought I told you
to go get the groceries.

23:38.960 --> 23:40.710
- You mean the bourbon?

23:43.420 --> 23:46.000
I'll be right back, baby girl.

23:46.000 --> 23:48.330
- Don't go daddy.

23:48.330 --> 23:49.920
- Be right back.

24:00.290 --> 24:02.080
- It's weird.

24:02.080 --> 24:04.880
I keep going back to a place
I forgot about years ago.

24:04.880 --> 24:07.540
And all I find there's pain.

24:07.540 --> 24:10.460
- Look, this is
really hard for me.

24:10.460 --> 24:12.580
I want to help,
but I'm still pretty upset

24:12.580 --> 24:14.750
about what happened.

24:14.750 --> 24:16.710
- God, I'm sorry.

24:16.710 --> 24:18.790
I should not have asked you
to come over here.

24:18.790 --> 24:21.500
- I understand
it wasn't your doing,

24:21.500 --> 24:23.540
but I can't help
feeling what I feel.

24:23.540 --> 24:25.170
- I get it.

24:25.170 --> 24:27.330
I feel like I'm deceiving
people into thinking

24:27.330 --> 24:30.670
I'm back to my old self
and I'm not.

24:30.670 --> 24:34.000
I mean, I felt like an imposter
when both my legs worked.

24:37.330 --> 24:40.460
You've become
very important to me.

24:41.960 --> 24:43.540
(baby crying)

24:43.540 --> 24:44.830
I'll be right back.

24:48.330 --> 24:49.420
- Hey.
- Hey.

24:49.420 --> 24:50.710
- I'm coming baby girl.

24:50.710 --> 24:52.880
- For you, for tonight.

24:52.880 --> 24:54.460
- It's a backstage badge,
parking pass,

24:54.460 --> 24:56.250
everything you need.
- Thanks.

24:56.250 --> 24:58.250
I don't know if I'm going, but.

24:58.250 --> 25:00.210
- Oh, well, if you decide to.

25:00.210 --> 25:02.380
You know, thank you
for being so amazing

25:02.380 --> 25:04.170
and accepting through all this.

25:04.170 --> 25:06.120
- Well, I mean, I guess
the label's decision's best.

25:06.120 --> 25:07.960
- The label's decision?

25:07.960 --> 25:10.830
- About her going it
alone tonight.

25:10.830 --> 25:13.460
- Right.

25:13.460 --> 25:15.290
Well, you know how that goes.

25:18.580 --> 25:20.880
Oh, I can take her.

25:22.670 --> 25:25.120
- What?

25:25.120 --> 25:29.830
- You selfish,
narcissistic bitch.

25:31.330 --> 25:34.500
- Hallie, please give me
a chance to explain.

25:34.500 --> 25:35.710
- I knew it.

25:35.710 --> 25:38.040
I knew it was your call
all along.

25:38.040 --> 25:39.830
You know, you're right.

25:39.830 --> 25:41.330
You are deceiving your fans.

25:41.330 --> 25:43.580
You're deceiving everyone.

25:43.580 --> 25:47.790
- I can't go back out there
after all this time

25:47.790 --> 25:50.540
and promote something that
nobody gave a crap about.

25:50.540 --> 25:53.250
- Oh, well, if that's how you
feel about the album, fine.

25:53.250 --> 25:56.830
But I defended you
in front of people I love,

25:56.830 --> 26:00.080
who put their trust in me.
Do you know what that's like?

26:00.080 --> 26:02.170
- I'm sorry, okay,
I am so incredibly sorry.

26:02.170 --> 26:05.080
- No, no, I got to go.

26:05.080 --> 26:08.250
- Hallie, I really do
care about you.

26:08.250 --> 26:10.420
- There's only one person
you care about.

26:34.000 --> 26:35.620
- Yes?

26:35.620 --> 26:37.420
- Uh, actually, I was gonna...
- Daria? I mean...

26:37.420 --> 26:40.120
(knock on door)

26:40.120 --> 26:42.330
- One second!
Quick hide, go over there.

26:42.330 --> 26:43.580
- Daphne open the door.

26:43.580 --> 26:44.750
Come on, now.

26:47.040 --> 26:49.670
- How can I help you?
- What is this?

26:49.670 --> 26:51.380
- Oh my god, are you okay?

26:51.380 --> 26:53.040
- It's not mine, all right,

26:53.040 --> 26:54.500
I found it in the trash
in my bathroom.

26:54.500 --> 26:56.080
Now, what is it?

26:56.080 --> 26:57.250
- I don't know, ask Madie.

27:01.040 --> 27:02.380
- What have you been
doing here all night?

27:02.380 --> 27:03.920
- Sleeping.

27:03.920 --> 27:05.540
What do you do
in your room all night?

27:05.540 --> 27:07.500
- Don't start with me.

27:07.500 --> 27:10.120
- I'm not, I'm hoping this is
the end of the conversation.

27:15.920 --> 27:18.290
- Dude.

27:18.290 --> 27:20.880
You're right, he's clueless.
- Yeah...

27:20.880 --> 27:22.080
(door opens)

27:25.830 --> 27:28.330
- Who is this?

27:28.330 --> 27:30.620
- I can explain.

27:30.620 --> 27:32.040
- Well then you better
get to it.

27:34.750 --> 27:36.000
- Hey.
- Hey.

27:38.540 --> 27:40.960
- So uh, Emily told me
what happened.

27:43.040 --> 27:45.920
- Let me guess,
you're on her side.

27:45.920 --> 27:48.620
- You know I'm always
on your side.

27:48.620 --> 27:50.120
- Am I narcissistic?

27:55.420 --> 27:57.380
Forget I asked.

27:57.380 --> 27:59.540
- You can't think
about that now, Juliette,

27:59.540 --> 28:00.750
I mean, you're in
over your head.

28:00.750 --> 28:02.710
You just have to
get through this.

28:02.710 --> 28:05.040
- You think I should cancel.

28:05.040 --> 28:07.210
- I can't make that
decision for you.

28:07.210 --> 28:11.710
But I do think you should be
talking to someone.

28:11.710 --> 28:14.000
- There is no way I can handle
a stranger right now.

28:14.000 --> 28:16.420
- How about apologizing
to the choir at least.

28:18.290 --> 28:19.380
- They wouldn't listen to me.

28:19.380 --> 28:20.460
- How do you know?

28:20.460 --> 28:23.960
Be honest. You made a mistake.

28:23.960 --> 28:26.330
- You think so?

28:26.330 --> 28:28.880
Because I have no idea anymore.

28:28.880 --> 28:30.080
I don't know what I'm doing.

28:34.040 --> 28:38.420
One thing I can say though...

28:38.420 --> 28:40.290
thank God I have you.

28:45.710 --> 28:48.000
Thank you for not running away.

28:48.000 --> 28:51.120
There are so many other people
that would have.

28:52.670 --> 28:56.290
(baby coos)

28:56.290 --> 28:57.830
What do you think baby girl?

29:11.830 --> 29:13.290
- Come on baby,
let's go inside.

29:13.290 --> 29:14.880
It's too dark now.

29:14.880 --> 29:16.330
- When's daddy coming
to help me finish.

29:16.330 --> 29:17.460
- Look, something
happened to daddy

29:17.460 --> 29:18.500
and he's not coming home, okay?

29:18.500 --> 29:19.710
He's not coming home!

29:24.960 --> 29:28.330
- Let's get out of here
and go get something to eat.

29:33.210 --> 29:35.210
- Wait.

29:36.750 --> 29:39.580
- Please, there's
something I need to say.

29:39.580 --> 29:42.330
- And we should listen because?

29:47.080 --> 29:49.960
- Because you have never thought
you were going to be paralyzed

29:49.960 --> 29:54.000
for the rest of your life,
and now I'm not.

29:54.000 --> 29:56.500
And I'm still afraid.

29:56.500 --> 29:57.790
Afraid of failing,

29:57.790 --> 30:00.750
afraid of limping out
onto that stage

30:00.750 --> 30:03.040
in front of thousands of fans

30:03.040 --> 30:06.710
and making a fool out of myself.

30:06.710 --> 30:11.500
I live with that fear
every second of every day.

30:11.500 --> 30:13.670
And sometimes,

30:13.670 --> 30:16.420
out of that fear
I make poor decisions.

30:19.750 --> 30:23.880
It was my choice to pull you
out of tonight's show.

30:23.880 --> 30:26.380
And there will not be
a mini tour.

30:26.380 --> 30:27.580
Tonight was it.

30:32.540 --> 30:33.620
It's a tough world.

30:33.620 --> 30:35.330
The album didn't work.

30:35.330 --> 30:38.290
We love it but the fans
and the critics, they didn't.

30:38.290 --> 30:41.620
And I'm sorry.
That's on me.

30:41.620 --> 30:44.920
But I still want to see this
through to the end,

30:44.920 --> 30:46.500
no matter what anybody says.

30:50.290 --> 30:52.830
Will you please
sing with me tonight?

30:54.790 --> 30:57.830
- Why should we be there
for you now?

30:57.830 --> 31:00.170
- I'm not saying you should be.

31:00.170 --> 31:01.880
I'm just hoping you will.

31:07.170 --> 31:09.000
- No, okay,
she cannot stay here.

31:09.000 --> 31:11.580
- I don't understand
the big deal.

31:11.580 --> 31:13.580
- You found this girl
on the street, sweetheart.

31:13.580 --> 31:15.500
- Yes, exactly, and that's
why I brought her here.

31:15.500 --> 31:17.290
- Baby, I'm sorry,

31:17.290 --> 31:18.960
we can't be harboring homeless
kids here, all right?

31:18.960 --> 31:20.000
There are laws.

31:20.000 --> 31:22.380
- That's fine.

31:22.380 --> 31:24.170
I'll go.

31:29.750 --> 31:33.000
- Hold on.

31:33.000 --> 31:36.290
Do you mind me asking
how old you are?

31:36.290 --> 31:37.670
- I'm old enough.

31:37.670 --> 31:39.290
- If you want our help,

31:39.290 --> 31:42.120
I appreciate a little
respect in return.

31:42.120 --> 31:43.290
- 15.

31:43.290 --> 31:44.830
- It's a little young
to be on the streets.

31:44.830 --> 31:46.380
- Do you have a better idea?

31:49.460 --> 31:50.710
- Where's your parents?

31:50.710 --> 31:51.750
- That's a good question.

31:51.750 --> 31:53.620
If you find them, let me know.

31:53.620 --> 31:55.670
- So who takes care of you?

31:55.670 --> 31:59.420
- I have friends,
we take care of each other.

31:59.420 --> 32:00.960
- And now she has me.

32:06.460 --> 32:08.580
- You can stay.

32:08.580 --> 32:10.620
Just for the time being
until we figure something out.

32:12.920 --> 32:15.120
Let's get some breakfast.

32:15.120 --> 32:18.290
- Thank you for
agreeing to see me.

32:20.250 --> 32:24.380
- Well, I don't have
much time, so.

32:24.380 --> 32:26.170
- I was a complete ass
yesterday.

32:26.170 --> 32:27.920
- I get it.

32:27.920 --> 32:29.330
You agree to uphold
any obligation

32:29.330 --> 32:30.960
the law would have you keep.

32:30.960 --> 32:32.750
I appreciate that, so.

32:32.750 --> 32:35.170
- I'm an idiot.

32:37.040 --> 32:38.540
I'm in love with you, Scarlett,

32:38.540 --> 32:40.710
and I want to be in this 100%.

32:40.710 --> 32:42.750
Let's do this the right way.

32:42.750 --> 32:44.420
We can make this work.

32:47.540 --> 32:50.210
- Don't say that.
You know it's not true.

32:52.960 --> 32:55.120
- It might be true.

32:55.120 --> 32:56.830
I want it to be true.

32:59.960 --> 33:02.750
- You mean no standards.
- (laughing)

33:05.040 --> 33:07.710
- All right, ladies,
I'm headed out.

33:07.710 --> 33:10.170
- Have fun.
- Yeah, Deacon, have fun.

33:13.750 --> 33:16.460
- You're going to listen
to Brittany, right?

33:16.460 --> 33:18.120
- Even though I'm 13

33:18.120 --> 33:19.790
and not one of my friends
has a baby sitter,

33:19.790 --> 33:23.460
for the 100th time, yes.

33:23.460 --> 33:28.170
- All right, I'm just
doing my best here.

33:28.170 --> 33:29.920
- Brittany, thank you, uh,

33:29.920 --> 33:31.750
you got my number,
I won't be long.

33:31.750 --> 33:32.920
- Bye, thanks, Deacon.

33:41.750 --> 33:44.830
- Billy, hey.
- Hey, Avery.

33:44.830 --> 33:46.290
- How you doing,
I'm looking forward

33:46.290 --> 33:47.420
to your girl's
big performance tonight.

33:47.420 --> 33:49.750
So tell me, she said yes?

33:49.750 --> 33:51.750
- That's what I need
to talk to you about.

33:51.750 --> 33:54.830
Um, I can't do it.

33:54.830 --> 33:56.500
- What do you mean?

33:56.500 --> 33:59.540
- It's just,
it's not the right time.

33:59.540 --> 34:04.380
You know, she needs me here
and I can't leave her.

34:04.380 --> 34:06.790
I'm sorry.

34:11.330 --> 34:13.120
- Still no sign of them.

34:16.290 --> 34:17.960
- Can you blame them?

34:29.120 --> 34:31.420
- Why are all these people here?

34:31.420 --> 34:34.420
- Baby, your daddy's gone,

34:34.420 --> 34:36.040
and, and, and he's
never coming back.

34:36.040 --> 34:39.290
- No, I want my daddy!

34:39.290 --> 34:40.290
- Juliette, come back here!

34:40.290 --> 34:42.540
Juliette!

34:44.920 --> 34:48.880
(crowd chanting)
- Juliette! Juliette!

34:52.830 --> 34:54.460
- Hey man.

34:54.460 --> 34:56.000
Just a minute, Bucky.

34:56.000 --> 34:57.210
Where you going?

35:02.500 --> 35:04.580
- I'm out, Deacon.

35:06.210 --> 35:07.750
- No, no, no,
you stay right here,

35:07.750 --> 35:09.330
he cannot fire you.
- Deacon, it was my idea.

35:09.330 --> 35:11.290
It's my idea.
If this is what he wants,

35:11.290 --> 35:12.790
this is the way
it's going to have to be.

35:12.790 --> 35:14.210
There's no way around it.

35:14.210 --> 35:15.790
- Yeah, we'll get
around it, Bucky,

35:15.790 --> 35:17.290
we'll get around it together,
we can do it.

35:17.290 --> 35:19.330
- Deacon, you cannot sacrifice
this company,

35:19.330 --> 35:22.250
your family, the girls,
for me.

35:22.250 --> 35:24.540
I won't let you.

35:24.540 --> 35:26.330
I'll be all right.

35:27.750 --> 35:29.460
Just be careful,

35:29.460 --> 35:31.920
because I got the feeling
I'm only the first.

35:47.620 --> 35:49.540
- What did I do?
- You know what you did.

35:49.540 --> 35:51.960
- Deacon, I'm just looking out
for this company, Deacon.

36:02.500 --> 36:05.250
(crowd chanting)
- Juliette! Juliette!

36:12.460 --> 36:15.420
- You came.

36:15.420 --> 36:16.880
- We came.

36:25.580 --> 36:27.710
- We really need to go,
Miss Barnes.

36:27.710 --> 36:30.920
- Then you better get
the choir on stage.

36:35.250 --> 36:39.330
(choir vocalizing)
(band plays)

37:03.120 --> 37:04.960
